     - Large \(k\): \(O(q \cdot \sqrt{n})\) in the worst case (if all queries are large \(k\)).
     - Small \(k\): \(O(q \log n)\) for binary searches and \(O(q \cdot \sqrt{n})\) for applying the batch updates.
